ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: yes, this class teaches very marketable and usefull skills
This class is excellent for students who are looking to understand and improve industry from an environmental perspective.

I would recommend this class to any engineer at the School of Engineering and Applied Sciences. The project provides a real world problem different to anything that I've ever done in the past. I thought it was excellent.

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: This class is very relevant to my discipline
As a student focused on energy and resources, the course helped me consider the energy industry from a new ecosystem perspective.
This course helped me to better understand system solutions to problems and a new way of thinking when designing for new projects. The system perspective solutions are really insightful.
